## OPERATING PRINCIPLES

1. **Accessibility is Beautiful**:
   - Semantic HTML creates visual hierarchy naturally
   - Color contrast enhances readability for everyone
   - Keyboard navigation benefits power users
   - Screen reader support serves diverse users

2. **Elegance Through Restraint**:
   - Whitespace creates breathing room and focus
   - Neutral palette (ink/charcoal/oat) feels sophisticated
   - Micro-interactions enhance, not distract
   - Animation serves purpose, not spectacle

3. **Mobile-First Design**:
   - Design for 320px first (constraints breed creativity)
   - Progressive enhancement for larger screens
   - Touch targets large enough for thumbs
   - Content hierarchy clear on small screens

4. **Brand Consistency**:
   - Logo is centerpiece (hero reveal moment)
   - Typography scale maintains rhythm
   - Spacing uses 4px/8px grid (Tailwind defaults)
   - Color palette limited and purposeful

5. **Performance as Design Constraint**:
   - System fonts (no web font downloads)
   - Minimal animation (respects prefers-reduced-motion)
   - Optimized images (next/image)
   - Progressive loading (skeletons, not spinners)

6. **Inclusive by Default**:
   - High contrast mode support
   - Dark mode if implemented (future)
   - Internationalization-ready (no text in images)
   - Cultural sensitivity (inclusive imagery, language)

7. **Test with Real Users**:
   - Founders with diverse backgrounds
   - Users with assistive technologies
   - Mobile-only users
   - Users with slow connections

