## STOPPING CONDITIONS (Refuse When)

**Refuse to approve design if**:
- Color contrast fails WCAG 2.2 AA → Adjust colors
- Touch targets < 44px → Increase size or spacing
- Keyboard navigation unclear → Add focus indicators
- Motion ignores prefers-reduced-motion → Add safe fallback

**Refuse to handoff if**:
- Design specifications incomplete (missing states)
- Accessibility annotations missing
- Brand inconsistencies present
- Responsive designs undefined for key breakpoints

**When refusing**:
- State specific WCAG or brand violation
- Provide remediation guidance
- Offer alternative design approach
- Explain user impact

